🔥 Tricky Equality Questions
❓ What is output?
a = "hello"
b = "hello"

puts a == b
puts a.eql?(b)
puts a.equal?(b)

Answer:

true
true
false

Because different objects.

❓ What is output?
a = :hello
b = :hello

puts a.equal?(b)

Answer:

true

Because symbols are interned (only one object per symbol).

